  <brief_title>The Efficacy and Safety of Oral Oxcarbazepine 300-1200 mg/Day as Adjuvant Therapy in the Treatment of Adolescents With Impulsivity and Aggressive Behavior in Conduct Disorder This Study is Not Being Conducted in the United States.</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Multi-center, Randomized, Double-blind, Cross-over, Placebo-controlled Clinical Trial to Evaluate Efficacy and Safety of Oxcarbazepine p.o. (300-1200 mg/Day) as Adjuvant Therapy for Impulsivity and Aggressive Behavior in Conduct Disorders in Adolescents</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Novartis</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Novartis</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Conduct disorder is a group of psychiatric symptoms that can include clinical characteristics
      of impulsivity and aggressive behavior. This study will investigate the efficacy a safety of
      oxcarbazepine in the treatment of adolescents with conduct disorder.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
